Arrays
Arrays are used to store multiple values in a single variable. Each element in an array is accessed using an index. You can iterate over arrays and modify elements.
1 variable = multiple values
[root@localhost scripting]# cat  array.sh
#!/bin/bash
fruits=("appple,mango,grapes")
for fruit in "${fruits[@]}";do
        echo $fruit
done
[root@localhost scripting]# bash array.sh
appple,mango,grapes
